# AI Coordination Engine - Bot Project
Created: 2026-03-03
Status: ✅ COMPLETE

## All Implementation Complete:

### Core:
- ✅ Project structure (config/, db/, ai/, bot/, tests/)
- ✅ Database models (8 tables: users, groups, events, constraints, reputation, logs, feedback, ailog)
- ✅ Database schema (db/schema.sql)
- ✅ Hybrid AI engine (rules + LLM fallback)
- ✅ Telegram bot (polling mode with ApplicationBuilder)

### Command Handlers (12):
- ✅ /start - Welcome message with help
- ✅ /organize_event - Create event with time, threshold, invitees
- ✅ /join - Mark attendance intent
- ✅ /confirm - Confirm attendance
- ✅ /cancel - Cancel with nudges
- ✅ /constraints - View/add/remove constraints
- ✅ /suggest_time - Request AI time suggestions
- ✅ /status - Show event progress
- ✅ /event_details - Show event details
- ✅ /my_groups - List user groups
- ✅ /profile - User profile
- ✅ /reputation - Check reputation

### Features:
- ✅ Event state machine (proposed→interested→confirmed→locked→completed)
- ✅ Soft friction nudges (fallback warnings, reliability warnings, deadline warnings)
- ✅ Inline keyboards for interactive flows
- ✅ Post-event feedback collection
- ✅ Full async/await throughout

### Infrastructure:
- ✅ Docker configuration (bot.Dockerfile)
- ✅ docker-compose.yml (bot + PostgreSQL)
- ✅ .dockerignore
- ✅ Environment configuration (.env.example)

### Testing:
- ✅ test_setup.py - Import and DB connection tests
- ✅ pytest test suite structure ready

## Usage:
```bash
# Run tests
export TELEGRAM_TOKEN="test_token"
python3 test_setup.py

# Start bot
python main.py

# Database setup
docker run -d --name coord_bot_db -e POSTGRES_USER=coord_user -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=coord_pass -e POSTGRES_DB=coord_db -p 5432:5432 postgres:15
psql -h localhost -U coord_user -d coord_db -f db/schema.sql
```

## AI Setup:
- Local Qwen3 at http://127.0.0.1:8080
- Or configure OpenAI-compatible endpoint in .env